## Database Tables for State Persistence

### `saga_executions` Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE saga_executions (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    current_state VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    context JSONB NOT NULL,           -- stores all order data
    completed_steps TEXT[] NOT NULL,  -- array of completed step names
    failed_step VARCHAR(100),
    retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
);
```

### `dead_letter_queue` Table
```sql
CREATE TABLE dead_letter_queue (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    failed_step VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    context JSONB NOT NULL,
    error_message TEXT,
    retry_attempts INTEGER,
    status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'PENDING', -- PENDING, RESOLVED, RETRYING
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    resolved_at TIMESTAMP
);
```

